<br>
1. Keep moving. Kill those baddies as fast as you can and keep going. Only stop and med/heal once you are totaly oom and short on life. Mana comes slow at lower levels, so when you take breaks make sure you need to.<br>
<br>
2. Most of the lower season crowed doesnt have high resists. If you run into a enchanter baddie, kill it first. That enchanter will screw you hard and fast. Mez is a pain in the ass. <br>
<br>
3. Make sure you got healers. Cleric if possible, shammy, druid will work. If you dont, your toast. <br>
<br>
4. If you can get an enchanter, do it. Mezs roxxors. Life will be easier if you do. <br>
<br>
5. Bring a rogue who knows what they are doing. None of the lower seasons will be able to disarm/remove the traps or unlock the locks. As a rogue, I can tell ya, its a bitch to keep the traps disarmed as is. When you detect the trap, you whip around and look at it. Rather annoying but it wont let you miss it. <br>
<br>
6. If you wipe, and you will, dont waste time on rezs unless one of your members is far far away. Bind at the wayfayers camp before you go. Run back. The time it takes to run back is about the same as waiting on mana, healing and res effects. <br>
<br>
7. Buff outside before heading in. You got 30 minutes to get there, so use that time to buff and sow your self if able. <br>
<br>
8. On rescue missions have one of your members grab em and book it. The rest of yall just clean out anything you didnt kill on the way there. I lost my one and only rescue mission so far because of monsters we left behind and didnt clear out. <br>
<br>
9. Beprepared for crappy loot and points. Augs I've seen so far havent broken +2. Its expected since you are lower in seasons but any augs are fun. But dont expect em. My first mission I didnt find any next two I found three and my last I got nothin. I'm not sure how the point system works for lower seasons, but I only got 1 for my first completed,and I got 0 for my second. Lost the other two. <br>
<br>
10. Last, but not least, dont turn any class down. You can use em all and no one class, besides a healer, will break you. All the classes I've grouped with are worth the spot.<br>
<br>
